</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FFCE3916EBD2C346FB225F86" blockId="96.[226,1437,1141,1201]" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">
A single otolith from the Piney Point Formation, 
<collectingRegion id="C317DF87FFCE3916E811C346FC7C5FB9" box="[800,899,1141,1167]" country="United States of America" name="Virginia" pageId="96" pageNumber="97">Virginia</collectingRegion>
, has the typical sulcus pattern of antennariids. A more precise taxonomic evaluation is not possible just on the basis of that specimen.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
